One of points of the article is that if you write a+b then compiler is free to assume that no overflow happens. If the compiler was sufficiently smart then if you wrote<p><pre><code>   if(checked_addr(a,b,rp)) {
       //something 1
   } else {
       //something 2
   }
</code></pre>
then compiler is free to assume no overflow happens and replace code with:<p><pre><code>    checked_add(a,b,rp);
    //something 2</code></pre>
